Reference

Running code

Main files for running the model and plotting its output

key_run()

Key_Run (Length-based Multispecies Analysis by numerical Simulation)

plot_key_run()

Plots output from the key_run script

Data

Data files included with package, taken from Rochet et al (2011)

rochet_GB_foodweb

Foodweb: who eats whom

rochet_GB_initialValues

Intitial abundance values

rochet_GB_modelSetup

List of species independent parameters

rochet_GB_parameterValues

Parameter values used in the model

rochet_GB_species

Species descriptions

LeMANS LeMANS-package

LeMANS: Length-based Multispecies Analysis by Numerical Simulation

Intermediate

Intermediate functions called by key_run.

calc_F()

Calculate fishing Mortality

calc_M1()

Calculates M1 mortality

calc_M2_c()

Calculates predation mortality, M2 (C++)

calc_maturity()

Calculates Maturity

calc_phi()

Calculates the proportion of individuals that leave a size class

calc_population_growth()

Calculates the change in the poulation in each time step

calc_ration()

Calculate species ration, growth efficiency, and size class weight

calc_recruits()

Calculates recruits and spawning stock biomass (SSB)

calc_sizepref_suitability()

Calculates size preference and suitabilities
